# Error Handling System

Error handling ensures system resilience.

No user action should cause app failure.

---

# Product Vision

Error system must:

- prevent crashes
- recover gracefully
- retry intelligently
- show meaningful feedback
- preserve user state

---

# Architecture

ErrorController

↓

ErrorState

↓

ErrorLogger

↓

RetryManager

↓

Fallback UI System

---

# Error Categories

- Network Errors
- API Errors
- AI Errors
- Sync Errors
- Validation Errors
- System Errors

---

# Global Rules

- never expose raw error codes to users
- always provide user-friendly messages
- always preserve user state
- retry silently when possible

---

# Retry Strategy

- exponential backoff
- max retry limits
- fallback after failure threshold

---

# Offline Behaviour

- detect offline state
- queue actions
- show offline mode UI

---

# UI Fallback Rules

- skeleton loading
- cached data fallback
- retry button only when necessary

---

# Logging Rules

- log all errors internally
- group similar errors
- avoid duplicate logs

---

# API Contracts

POST /errors/log

GET /errors/report

---

# Performance Rules

- error handling must not block UI
- retries must be async

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Retry logic

Error classification

Fallback behavior

Integration Tests:

API failure recovery

Offline error handling

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating features:

- always handle failure states
- always preserve user data
- always provide fallback UI
- never crash silently